President Donald J. Trump met with President Pedro Pablo Kuczynski of Peru to discuss ways to strengthen the collaboration between the United States and Peru. They emphasized the commitment to expand trade and investment ties with Peru and other countries in the Asia-Pacific region. The leaders also discussed the fight against transnational organized crime and explored options for closer defense and security collaboration. Both expressed concerns about the political and economic situation in Venezuela and the need for collaboration among Western Hemisphere leaders to preserve democratic institutions in that country. President Trump also thanked Peru for hosting the 8th meeting of the Summit of the Americas next year.